  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This randomised, controlled, double blinded clinical study investigates the safety and
      efficacy of the combination of albendazole, ivermectin and praziquantel in the treatment of
      children aged 5-18 years co-infected with lymphatic filariasis, schistosomiasis and
      soil-transmitted helminthiasis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
